      <prefercite id="aspace_f9e55ac8ea4e8ffa0f67892de077e257">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Henry Crosby Emery Papers (MS 966). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_e0b9a44519f29114aceacdac5ea20e43">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Mrs. H. C. Emery, 1924.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_2904e89c33eb4cd9af22eba6973adb55">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Henry Crosby Emery: economist; B.A., Bowdoin, 1892; M.A., Harvard, 1893; Ph.D., Columbia, 1896; professor at Bowdoin, 1896-1900; professor of political economy at Yale, 1900-1915; president of U.S. Tariff Board, 1909-1913; worked for Guaranty Trust Co., 1917-1924.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_34a88f572f76aa4de8ecdb1f0c8450ed">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers center on two aspects of Emery's activities: his teaching career at Yale and his service as chairman of the U.S. Tariff Board (1909-1913). Papers relating to the Board include correspondence, reports, statistics, and cloth samples collected in connection with the board's investigation of the carpet, wool, and cotton manufacturing industries, ca.1911-1912. Principal correspondents are members of the board, among them Alvin H. Sanders, James B. Reynolds, L. M. Spier, N. I. Stone, R. B. Horrow, and Charles A. Veditz.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_0982244b01cd1b49b14fe3f79b9d0f00">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged in two series: I. Correspondence. II. Topical Files.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_1459196a7f2673118ce062e067bd2fff">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
